WEBVTT

00:01:59.149 --> 00:02:02.149
through those questions, we as teachers have information

00:02:02.149 --> 00:02:05.177
that we can use to tailor robust

00:02:05.177 --> 00:02:08.868
and informed methods of blended instruction.

00:02:08.868 --> 00:02:14.040
So, 21st-century lingo jargon mumbo jumbo aside,

00:02:14.040 --> 00:02:18.244
the truth is, I've been teaching for 13 years now,

00:02:18.244 --> 00:02:20.718
and it took a life-threatening situation

00:02:20.718 --> 00:02:23.665
to snap me out of 10 years of pseudo-teaching

00:02:23.665 --> 00:02:27.280
and help me realize that student questions

00:02:27.280 --> 00:02:30.401
are the seeds of real learning,